  "body": "We use [smock](https://github.com/defi-wonderland/smock) to handle mocking/faking within the tests for the contracts package. We're currently using an older and unnecessary of creating `FakeContract` objects:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/99021e29798ce04e1fcad95cae7e655b7e346e68/packages/contracts/test/contracts/L1/messaging/L1CrossDomainMessenger.spec.ts#L72-L74\r\n\r\nSpecifically, a `FakeContract` can be created more simply like so:\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nFake__TargetContract = await smock.fake<Contract>('Helper_SimpleProxy')\r\n```\r\n\r\nDifference here is that the first parameter to the `fake` function is a string instead of a `ContractFactory` object. Goal of this issue is to update all instances of `smock.fake` to take a string as the first parameter. It's slightly cleaner.\r\n\r\nI recommend searching for `smock.fake` and fixing every instance that you find. Should be pretty easy!",
